Why Intent Data Is the Game Changer 

If there is one concept that separates modern B2B marketing from legacy approaches, it is intent data. Intent data refers to behavioral signals collected from a buyer's online activity — the content they consume, the searches they conduct, the topics they engage with — that indicate their likelihood to purchase.

In 2026, intent data is not just a competitive advantage. It is a necessity for any organization serious about efficient pipeline generation.

Here is why intent data matters so profoundly for understanding and engaging modern B2B buyers:

Timing Is Everything in B2B Sales: Research consistently shows that the first vendor to engage a prospect who is actively in-market wins the deal at a dramatically higher rate. Intent data tells you when a prospect is researching relevant topics, giving your sales team the opportunity to reach out at precisely the right moment — when the buyer is already primed to have a conversation.

Prioritization of High-Value Accounts: Not every account in your CRM is equally likely to buy. Intent data allows you to score and prioritize accounts based on demonstrated buying signals, so your sales and marketing resources are focused on the opportunities most likely to convert.

Personalization at Scale: When you know what a prospect has been researching, you can tailor your outreach to speak directly to their interests and concerns. This level of relevance dramatically improves response rates, engagement, and ultimately, conversion.

Reduced Wasted Spend: Without intent data, marketing budgets are often spread too thin across accounts that have no near-term buying intent. Intent-driven campaigns concentrate your investment where it will generate the highest return.

